-- Mitsubishi All-Wheel Drives Tested on Icy Roads: Video
-- 
-- 2010-03-04T15:21:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-03-04/mitsubishi-all-wheel-drives-tested-on-icy-roads-video.html

          
          
             Mitsubishi Motors Corp. all-wheel 
drive vehicles are tested on ice-slicked woodland roads in 
northern New Hampshire in this video provided by Mitsubishi. 
(Source: Mitsubishi Motors North America)  
 Running time 00:45  
 -0- Mar/04/2010 15:21 GMT
  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     Tim O'Neil, owner of Team O'Neil Rally School, drives a 2010 Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution MR on a snowy track at Team O'Neil Rally School in Dalton, New Hampshire. The school is set in a private 560-acre valley and consists of a 6.5-mile forest road course, separate skid pad and braking zone, obstacle avoidance area and a slalom course. Photographer: Herb Swanson/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     A 2010 Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution MR on a snowy track at Team O'Neil Rally School in Dalton, New Hampshire. This year’s brutal winter in much of the U.S. and Europe
shows all drivers can use snow-surviving, slip-sliding skills. Photographer: Herb Swanson/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     A 2010 Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution MR on a snowy track at Team O'Neil Rally School in Dalton, New Hampshire. Rally racing is a popular motorsport worldwide that is set on real roads with little traction like gravel, ice or dirt. Photographer: Herb Swanson/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     A Subaru rally car on a snowy track at Team O'Neil Rally School in Dalton, New Hampshire. The school is set in a private 560-acre valley and consists of a 6.5-mile forest road course, separate skid pad and braking zone, obstacle avoidance area, and a slalom course. Photographer: Herb Swanson/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     A 2010 Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution MR is driven on a snowy skid pad at Team O'Neil Rally School in Dalton, New Hampshire. Mitsubishi’s goal was to show that its AWD technology is as sharp as better-known competitors like Audi and Subaru. Photographer: Herb Swanson/Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
                     A 2010 Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution MR on a snowy skid pad at Team O'Neil Rally School in Dalton, New Hampshire. Photographer: Herb Swanson/Bloomberg  
                           

     
